Minimap2 Assembly-to-Assembly Alignment Pipeline (v2.28-r1209)\
==============================================================\
\
Description:\
    This pipeline uses Minimap2 to perform a rapid, sensitive alignment of a query genome \
    or assembly against a reference genome. It is optimized for large-scale, whole-genome \
    comparison tasks, often used in comparative genomics or scaffold placement.\
\
Key Features:\
    1. Two-Step Optimization: Splits the process into a single, efficient **indexing** step \
       and a subsequent, fast **mapping** step, minimizing redundant computation when \
       the reference is reused.\
    2. Preset Configuration: Uses the `-x asm5` preset, which configures Minimap2 with \
       parameters (k-mer size, minimum match length, etc.) optimized for high-quality \
       assembly-to-assembly alignment, offering a balance of speed and sensitivity.\
    3. Output Format: The alignment results are written to a **PAF (Pairwise mApping Format)** file, a standard tab-delimited format detailing the mappings.\
\
Commands:\
    1. Indexing (`-d`): Builds the reference index file (`.mmi`).\
    2. Mapping: Aligns query sequences to the reference using the index file.\
\
Purpose:\
    To generate the initial alignment data (PAF) required for downstream analysis, \
    such as identifying synteny, structural variants, or performing quality control \
    on assembly contigs.\
